Step 1: Let T \propto l^a m^b g^c
Or, T = k l^a m^b g^c \quad \text{(k = dimensionless constant)}

Step 2: Write dimensional formula:
[T] = [L]^a [M]^b [LT^{-2}]^c

Step 3: Simplify:
[M^0L^0T^1] = [M^b L^{a+c} T^{-2c}]

Step 4: Equate powers:
For M: b = 0
For T: -2c = 1 \Rightarrow c = -\frac{1}{2}
For L: a + c = 0 \Rightarrow a = -c = \frac{1}{2}

Step 5: Substitute values:
T = k l^{1/2} m^0 g^{-1/2}
T = k \sqrt{\frac{l}{g}}

Experimentally, k = 2\pi
\therefore T = 2\pi \sqrt{\frac{l}{g}}

Dimensional formula of force = [MLT^{-2}]

In CGS: M_1 = g, L_1 = cm, T_1 = s
In SI: M_2 = kg, L_2 = m, T_2 = s

n_2 = n_1 \left[\frac{M_1}{M_2}\right]^1 \left[\frac{L_1}{L_2}\right]^1 \left[\frac{T_1}{T_2}\right]^{-2}

n_2 = 50 \left[\frac{1g}{1kg}\right] \left[\frac{1cm}{1m}\right] \left[\frac{1s}{1s}\right]^{-2}

n_2 = 50 \left[\frac{1}{1000}\right] \left[\frac{1}{100}\right] [1]^{-2}

n_2 = 50 \times 10^{-3} \times 10^{-2} = 50 \times 10^{-5}

\therefore 50 \text{ dyne} = 5 \times 10^{-4} \text{ N}

72 \text{ km/h} = 72 \times \frac{1000 \text{ m}}{3600 \text{ s}}

= 72 \times \frac{1000}{3600} \text{ m/s}

= 72 \times \frac{5}{18} \text{ m/s}

= 4 \times 5 = 20 \text{ m/s}
